The soldiers of the IDF, the Shin Bet and the Security Guard worked tonight to arrest four wanted persons throughout Judea and Samaria The soldiers of the IDF, the Shin Bet and the Mageb operated tonight in a number of locations in the Judea and Samaria Division, among others in the villages of Masarie a Nowani, Hizma, Tapuh and in the city of Hebron. The fighters operated in the village of Beit Deko in the area of the Binyamin regional division and arrested two wanted persons suspected of involvement in terrorist activity.

During the activity of the fighters in the city of Ramallah, in the sector of the Binyamin regional division, and in the village of Sheo'ah, in the sector of the Etzion regional division, suspects threw stones and threw Molotov cocktails at the force. The force responded with measures to disperse demonstrations In an operation in the village of Shio'ah, two wanted persons suspected of involvement in terrorist activities were arrested.

There are no casualties to our forces.

The arrested wanted persons were transferred for further investigation by the security forces

The IDF, Shin Bet, and Israel Defense Forces arrested nine wanted men across Judea and Samaria tonight. IDF, Shin Bet, and Israel Defense Forces soldiers operated tonight in several locations in the Judea and Samaria Division, among others in the Ein Beit Alma refugee camp > >

IDF soldiers operated in the village of Beit Omer and arrested two wanted persons suspected of involvement in terrorist activities. There are no casualties to our forces. The arrested wanted persons were transferred to the interrogation of the security forces

The forces operated in the Jilzon refugee camp in the Binyamin regional division and arrested one wanted person suspected of involvement in terrorist activities. During the activity, a violent disturbance developed with the participation of dozens of suspects who threw stones and threw an improvised explosive device at the force In addition, two suspects who were in the vehicle sped towards the force who started a suspect arrest procedure that included shooting at the suspects. Vulnerabilities have been detected.
